column5: one and a half hours on the ice and managed one keeper walleye and a 61cm/5lbs sow. She swam away, just a little angry...  The guys around us were going nuts apparently catching big ones as well.  I need a good camera, my ipod doesn't have a flash. Squint just right, and you'll see the big girl. I swear I havn't taken background blurring to a new level.
Looks like a real good fish(if i could see her)  Thats ok, i could see enough to know that it was a good'un. Nice Job !
Nice job Chad. I'll take you up on one of your offers.
Thanks guys.  We went again at 5 am this morning. One keeper walleye, a herring and tons of perch.
Nice BIG breeder to release back into the lake.....
You got them hawgs dialed in Chad   Awesome   WTG
Haha, Thanks to TJ and the Nipissing G2G.
